<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: experience ring?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Fenaorn">Fenaorn</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:29 p.m. 19/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: experience ring?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/erollisi_marr.cgi?read=79" TARGET=_self>experience ring?</A> (Dragn)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> One night in Greater Faydark, someone was

<BR>&gt; selling what he called an experience ring
<BR>&gt; for 100pp. However I never got to see it,
<BR>&gt; nor would he tell me where he got it. An
<BR>&gt; item that doubles experience earned per
<BR>&gt; battle is something that shouldn't be kept
<BR>&gt; secret from others. I often buy stuff from
<BR>&gt; people that give me locations of where they
<BR>&gt; got the items, and refuse to buy anything
<BR>&gt; from those who won't tell me and are rude
<BR>&gt; about it. What I want to know is: Does this
<BR>&gt; item really exist? I never got to see it so
<BR>&gt; I'm not sure. If it is real, where is it
<BR>&gt; found? Is it sold from an npc? Does a
<BR>&gt; monster of sorts drop it? If it is aquired
<BR>&gt; from a defeated monster, what level must one
<BR>&gt; be to defeat it? (Alone or in a group)
<P>I doubt very much that this item exists. An item that good would be much more popular. Verant making an item like this would make it VERY unfair. 2nd, Verant would not make an item that affected a stat that wouldn't have anything to do with our CHARACTER.. EXP is something that is out of game. It is not why your character goes around slaying monsters. A ring that increases STR, simply makes them stronger. Your character would like something like this.. but an EXP ring.. don't keep your hopes up:)
<P>Good luck!
<P>- Fenaorn Fizzmore
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
